it's our weekly
segment about the Leading Edge
of technology.

37:52.904 --> 37:58.143 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: They called it
Think Again,
Turn Away.

37:58.176 --> 38:00.278 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
The concept?

38:00.311 --> 38:06.818 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Use sarcasm as way to turn
Islamic State images
into an argument against their
grim techniques

38:06.851 --> 38:08.520 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of terror.

38:08.553 --> 38:10.522 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The creator and producer?

38:10.555 --> 38:13.825 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The U.S. State Department.

38:13.858 --> 38:18.296 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, everyone agrees the
message was worse
than ineffective.

38:18.329 --> 38:20.732 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It played right into the hands
of the terrorists.

38:20.765 --> 38:24.269 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
RICHARD STENGEL, U.S.
Undersecretary of State:
You know, part if it is that I
don't think

38:24.302 --> 38:27.505 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the government should do snark
or sarcasm.

38:27.539 --> 38:29.607 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I don't think we're good at it.

38:29.641 --> 38:35.079 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Richard Stengel
is the undersecretary
of state for public diplomacy
and public affairs.

38:35.113 --> 38:38.383 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He realized he was the one who
needed to think
again.

38:38.416 --> 38:42.854 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RICHARD STENGEL: So, one of the
things that
we realized is that we're not
the best messenger

38:42.887 --> 38:44.822 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for the message that we want to
