38:44.856 --> 38:48.226 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In fact, when we are a messenger
at all, they
use that against us.

38:48.259 --> 38:53.064 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: So they stopped
trying to do
it themselves, and hired some
marketing pros.

38:53.097 --> 38:56.201 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TONY SGRO, Advertising and
Marketing Veteran:
I think that they just -- it was
out of their

38:56.234 --> 38:57.969 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
league.

38:58.002 --> 39:01.206 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Tony Sgro is an
advertising
and marketing veteran who is
spearheading

39:01.239 --> 39:06.878 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a novel competition for college
students to
create a counter or alternative
narrative

39:06.911 --> 39:09.013 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to the Islamic State propaganda
campaign.

39:09.047 --> 39:13.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TONY SGRO: The government is not
the most
capable person to develop a
counternarrative

39:13.184 --> 39:14.385 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for a 21-year- old.

39:14.419 --> 39:15.853 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There's no credibility factor
there.

39:15.887 --> 39:19.691 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: The competition
is called Peer
to Peer.

39:19.724 --> 39:23.561 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Undergraduates at two dozen
schools all over
the world have participated.

39:23.595 --> 39:30.401 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Afghanistan, they created a
campaign that
included a talk show that
focused on understanding

39:30.435 --> 39:34.205 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
