million people.

39:38.042 --> 39:46.050 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Lahore University produced a
plea from students
to students to turn apathy into
empathy.

39:46.084 --> 39:54.025 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The winner of the competition
was the Rochester
Institute of Technology.

39:54.058 --> 39:57.829 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Students there came up with this
multiplatform
campaign.

39:57.862 --> 40:00.665 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MAN: Join the campaign.

40:00.698 --> 40:01.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WOMAN: Because it's time.

40:01.699 --> 40:02.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WOMAN: To ex-app.

40:02.834 --> 40:05.770 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TONY SGRO: It's beyond bombs,
bullets, and
drones.

40:05.803 --> 40:06.771 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It really is.

40:06.804 --> 40:08.139 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I mean, we need that stuff.

40:08.172 --> 40:10.875 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we really -- how are you
going to win
the hearts and minds?

40:10.908 --> 40:11.876 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's communications.

40:11.909 --> 40:13.544 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's a marketing communications
issue.

40:13.578 --> 40:16.314 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Countering the
messages is
one thing.

40:16.347 --> 40:19.384 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Trying to stop them from
spreading in the
first place is another.

40:19.417 --> 40:24.255 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For years, the social networking
platforms
took a laissez-faire approach to
this problem.

40:24.289 --> 40:26.658 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And it only got worse.

40:26.691 --> 40:29.994 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But in 2013, things started to
change.

40:30.028 --> 40:34.599 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
During a horrifying assault on a
shopping
mall in Nairobi, Kenya,
attackers with the

40:34.632 --> 40:42.140 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
al-Qaida affiliate Al-Shabaab
live-tweeted
for hours as they shot more than
175 people,

40:42.173 --> 40:43.875 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
killing 67.

40:43.908 --> 40:51.015 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFF WEYERS, Intelligence
Analyst: That was
the first time where Twitter was
actively

40:51.049 --> 40:52.884 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
removing the content that they
were posting.

40:52.917 --> 40:57.689 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Jeff Weyers is a
police officer
and terrorism analyst based in
Ontario, Canada.

40:57.722 --> 41:02.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFF WEYERS: They were actively
tweeting their
attack online, and it was the
first time we

41:02.293 --> 41:03.961 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
really saw that.

41:03.995 --> 41:06.297 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ISIS completely blew that out of
the water.

41:06.331 --> 41:07.465 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Right?

41:07.498 --> 41:10.301 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They took that concept and
magnified it by
a million.

41:10.335 --> 41:15.773 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Today, Twitter
claims it aggressively
goes after accounts linked to
terrorists.

41:15.807 --> 41:19.877 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The company says it closed
360,000 of them
in the past year.

41:19.911 --> 41:23.214 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFF WEYERS: They were very much
pushed into
it, as opposed to wanting to go
down that

41:23.247 --> 41:25.049 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
road.

41:25.083 --> 41:30.355 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And now I have no doubt that
they're spending
millions of dollars just
countering that message.

41:30.388 --> 41:36.794 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Facebook is the
largest social
networking platform on the
planet.

41:36.828 --> 41:42.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It says it has a zero tolerance
policy for
extremists, but it must contend
with a tsunami

41:42.734 --> 41:44.268 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of content.

41:44.302 --> 41:48.806 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Facebook has more than a billion
users actively
posting every day.

41:48.840 --> 41:53.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The company says about one-half
of 1 percent
of flagged items are linked to
terrorism.

41:53.644 --> 41:56.547 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But that is still a lot of
material.

41:56.581 --> 41:59.517 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Monika Bickert is Facebook's
head of global
policy management.

41:59.550 --> 42:03.221 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MONIKA BICKERT, Head of Global
Policy Management,
Facebook: We use photo-matching
technology

42:03.254 --> 42:08.459 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to identify when somebody is
trying to upload
to Facebook an image that we
have already

42:08.493 --> 42:11.129 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
removed for violation our
policies.

42:11.162 --> 42:16.501 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Of course, the image may or may
not violate
our policies when it's uploaded
again, because

42:16.534 --> 42:20.405 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it could be somebody who is
sharing a terrorist
image the Times Square part of a
news story

42:20.438 --> 42:22.273 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
or to condemn violence.

42:22.306 --> 42:27.211 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So we use automation to flag
content that
we will then have our teams
review.

42:27.245 --> 42:32.483 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: But are there
more advanced
ways to stop the extremist
messages from spreading?

42:32.517 --> 42:34.285 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Is there a better technological
solution?

42:34.318 --> 42:39.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HANY FARID, Dartmouth College:
We have the
technology to disrupt, not
eliminate, but

42:39.590 --> 42:44.762 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
to disrupt the global
transmission of
extremism-related
content.

42:44.796 --> 42:49.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Hany Farid is a
computer scientist
at Dartmouth College.

42:49.100 --> 42:55.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He has developed a technique to
permanently
attach unique digital signatures
to images,

42:55.072 --> 42:59.777 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
making it possible for the
social networking
companies to identify and stop
the spread

42:59.811 --> 43:03.414 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of videos made by, of and for
terror.

43:03.448 --> 43:08.586 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HANY FARID: So, here is the
actual raw frame
that you're seeing processing
one frame at

43:08.619 --> 43:09.954 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
a time.

43:09.987 --> 43:13.891 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And in the frame, we actually
analyze multiple
blocks within it.

43:13.925 --> 43:18.496 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The yellow crosshairs that
you're seeing are
enumerating the various blocks
of the video

43:18.529 --> 43:20.832 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that we're analyzing.

43:20.865 --> 43:24.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This yellow histogram is a
distribution of
the measurements that we're
making from each

43:24.936 --> 43:30.475 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
individual block, and then that
gets translated
into an actual digital
signature, which I

43:30.508 --> 43:32.577 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
visualize here with a stemplot.

43:32.610 --> 43:38.249 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: The sheer volume
of the problem
is daunting, billions of uploads
a day, each

43:38.282 --> 43:40.718 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of them with millions of pixels.

43:40.751 --> 43:46.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Can a computer possibly be
trained to sort
through it all and find the
images that inspire

43:46.123 --> 43:53.698 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
new recruits, incite new
violence and terrify
us all?

43:53.731 --> 43:56.734 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Farid has already proven the
technology works.

43:56.767 --> 43:58.970 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He got the idea 10 years ago.

43:59.003 --> 44:02.874 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Internet had become a
platform for child
pornographers.

44:02.907 --> 44:08.479 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Applying digital signatures to
those images
has greatly reduced child
pornography on the

44:08.513 --> 44:10.548 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
big social networking sites.

44:10.581 --> 44:15.987 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HANY FARID: So, if there's just
one image
in an upload of yours that has
child pornography,

44:16.020 --> 44:18.055 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
we -- the account can be frozen.

44:18.089 --> 44:21.626 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The contents of that account can
be assessed,
and new content can be
discovered.

44:21.659 --> 44:26.430 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: But extremist
content is much
harder to clearly define.

44:26.464 --> 44:31.335 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The director of the Free
Expression Project
at the Center for Democracy and
Technology

44:31.369 --> 44:33.070 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
is Emma Llanso.

44:33.104 --> 44:34.939 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EMMA LLANSO, Free Expression
Project: The
challenge with having a
hard-and-fast rule

44:34.972 --> 44:41.112 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
against any a kind of content is
that it really
does shut down the opportunity
for discussion

44:41.145 --> 44:42.880 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
around that sort of material.

44:42.914 --> 44:49.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: In June 2016,
David Thomson,
a French journalist who reports
on Islamic

44:49.086 --> 44:53.858 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
extremism, found his Facebook
page suspended
for three days.

44:53.891 --> 44:55.760 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
The offense?

44:55.793 --> 45:01.265 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A photo he had posted in 2013 as
part of the
story he was doing included a
partial depiction

45:01.299 --> 45:07.038 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the Islamic State flag, a
cautionary tale
of the unintended consequences
of targeting

45:07.071 --> 45:08.806 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
terrorism online.

45:08.839 --> 45:13.911 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EMMA LLANSO: It seems appealing
to say, oh,
just have the major social media
companies

45:13.945 --> 45:17.148 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
take a hard-line approach to
anything having
to do with ISIS.

45:17.181 --> 45:20.918 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the fact is, that will end
up blocking
a lot of speech.

45:20.952 --> 45:23.821 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That will end up deactivating
the accounts
of many users.

45:23.854 --> 45:28.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, some of the platforms
have had issues
with just deactivating the
accounts that women

45:28.125 --> 45:30.795 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
whose first name is Isis.

45:30.828 --> 45:34.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is a difficult kind of
censorship to
enact.

45:34.999 --> 45:40.037 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: It's no longer
just a war of
bullets, drones and bombs.

45:40.071 --> 45:47.278 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Technology has created a new
battlefield online,
and civil society is still
grasping for strategies

45:47.311 --> 45:50.381 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to engage in a virtual battle.

45:50.414 --> 45:52.683 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Miles O'Brien, the "PBS
NewsHour," Washington.

45:52.717 --> 45:59.390 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And you can watch
Miles' full
report, "15 Years of Terror,"
tonight on "NOVA"

45:59.423 --> 46:12.069 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
