were appropriate,
red, white and blue.

46:55.479 --> 47:00.651 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIKE CERRE: How this American
weaver from
Connecticut and her
Ethiopian-American husband

47:00.685 --> 47:06.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
helped save an endangered
traditional craft,
in a country ravaged by a secret
war the U.S.

47:06.590 --> 47:13.931 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
waged here during the Vietnam
War, is the
stuff of Southeast Asia lore.

47:13.964 --> 47:18.936 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Like Jim Thompson, the legendary
former CIA
agent who launched the Thai silk
industry

47:18.969 --> 47:24.241 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
after World War II, before he
mysteriously
disappeared, Carol Cassidy
helped resurrect

47:24.275 --> 47:27.511 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the traditional Lao textile
trade after their
war.

47:27.545 --> 47:34.251 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAROL CASSIDY: He had a great
idea, which
was to build a business based on
traditional

47:34.285 --> 47:35.786 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
skills.

47:35.820 --> 47:38.823 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's something that, here in
Laos, at Lao
Textiles, we have done as well.

47:38.856 --> 47:42.493 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
One of the important
distinctions is, I am
a weaver.

47:42.526 --> 47:47.932 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have devoted my entire life
since the age
of 17 to weaving one and
designing.

47:47.965 --> 47:52.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIKE CERRE: When she and her
husband came
here nearly 30 years ago as U.N.
development

47:52.903 --> 47:59.910 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
advisers, full diplomatic
relations between
the U.S. and Laos had yet to be
restored.

47:59.944 --> 48:05.049 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Americans were still viewed
somewhat suspiciously
by the communist Lao government,
the U.S.

48:05.082 --> 48:09.386 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
having been on the losing side
of the Laos
civil war and communist
takeover.

48:09.420 --> 48:16.060 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAROL CASSIDY: So it was really
this rebuilding
of Lao-American relations, that
we have felt

48:16.093 --> 48:17.895 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
that.

48:17.928 --> 48:21.999 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And my husband and I, who we
built the business
together, he is much more
diplomatic than

48:22.032 --> 48:23.601 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
I am.

48:23.634 --> 48:26.971 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think it's been very
helpful navigating
the complexities.

48:27.004 --> 48:31.408 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIKE CERRE: They eventually set
up a textile
business of their own with a
core staff of

48:31.442 --> 48:37.581 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
weavers from the north, many of
them the wives
and mothers of the Pathet Lao
communist forces

48:37.615 --> 48:42.219 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who had been living and working
out of caves
during the nearly 10 years of
U.S. bombing.

48:42.253 --> 48:45.923 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
CAROL CASSIDY: So, our
technology is very
simple.

48:45.956 --> 48:47.658 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's portable.

48:47.691 --> 48:53.831 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When they fled the bombing, they
were able
to take with them simple
technology and be

48:53.864 --> 48:55.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
able to keep their family
traditions.

48:55.766 --> 49:01.205 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MIKE CERRE: The work is
incredibly painstaking,
from the hand-dyeing of the
silk, to spinning

49:01.238 --> 49:08.279 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the silk yarn, and reproducing
traditional
designs from memory, using
traditional Lao

49:08.312 --> 49:13.951 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
looms many consider to be the
inspiration
for the first computers and
binary code.

49:13.984 --> 49:18.856 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAROL CASSIDY: The important
part is this
